Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Add @farro{1%cup}, 3 cups water, and a @salt{pinch} to a #medium pot{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer for ~{30-35%minutes}, until farro is tender. Drain any excess water.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @garlic{2%cloves}. Slice the @button mushrooms{4%ounce}. Chop the @parsley{1%bunch}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @yellow onion{1}. Thoroughly wash the @sunchokes{6%ounce}, then thinly slice into 1/4-inch rounds. Remove and discard the tough stems and ribs from the @Tuscan kale{1%bunch}, then thinly slice.

> Did you know? Never tried sunchokes? They're also known by the name Jerusalem Artichokes, which are the bulb of sunflower plants. They have a great starchy texture and similar flavor to sunflower seeds!

Toss the sunchokes on a #baking sheet{} with 1/2 tablespoon @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Place in the oven for ~{20%minutes}, until golden brown.

Meanwhile, heat 1 teaspoon @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook, tossing, for ~{5%minutes}, until golden brown. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

In the same pan, heat another 2 teaspoon of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} over medium heat. Add the onion and cook, tossing, for ~{5%minutes}, until soft. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the sliced kale and garlic to the pan with the softened onions and toss until wilted, adding a splash of water if necessary. Season with salt and pepper.

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @white wine vinegar{1%tablespoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Reserve half the dressing and set aside. Toss remaining dressing with the warm farro and chopped parsley.

Top the farro with the sauteed kale mixture, mushrooms, and sunchokes, then drizzle with remaining dressing. Sprinkle with @pepitas{1%ounce} and @goat cheese{2%ounce} and enjoy!